<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1326,1605]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<taxonomicName authority="Schiotz, 1982" authorityName="Schiotz" authorityYear="1982" box="[151,634,1399,1425]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="viridiflavus" subSpecies="reesi">
<emphasis box="[151,469,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius viridiflavus reesi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schiotz" box="[477,634,1399,1425]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="269 - 276" refId="ref34209" refString="Schiotz, A. (1982) Two new Hyperolius (Anura) from Tanzania. Steenstrupia, 8, 269 - 276." type="journal article" year="1982">Schiøtz, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. ZMUC 
<accessionNumber box="[733,825,1398,1425]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/R77205" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">R77205</accessionNumber>
, Magombero Forest, 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1168,1399,1425]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1229,1277,1399,1425]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">type</typeStatus>
was collected close to the localities of the sequenced material, and this form is known to be widely distributed on the central 
<collectingCountry box="[199,300,1471,1497]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
highlands (
<bibRefCitation author="Schiotz" box="[428,586,1471,1497]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref34233" refString="Schiotz, A. (1999) Treefrogs of Africa. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 350 pp." type="book" year="1999">Schiøtz, 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Phase J colour in life: back silvery-brown with a darker pattern of spots and an irregular hourglass pattern. Sides of head and body dark, without a subdermal dark lateral streak. Phase F: Back yellow to light green, flanks with a conspicuous subdermal lateral streak, overlain by 2–3 yellow vertical stripes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1651,2037]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
Sequences were available from Kibasira Swamp and Mang’ula, (close to Magombero Forest) 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1306,1651,1677]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1321,1423,1651,1677]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-63@40.[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 10. Localities of sequences (black circles), type localities (stars) and location of junior synonyms of Hyperolius noblei (A), H. goetzei (B), H. spatzi (C) and H. dintelmanni (D). Locality codes are explained in Table 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538300/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
). The minimum uncorrected 
<emphasis box="[457,480,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">p-</emphasis>
distances from other clades were 4.0–7.0% (
<tableCitation box="[976,1063,1687,1713]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="20.[151,239,762,788]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 2. Uncorrected minimum p-distances as percentages between the clades. GOE—Hyperolius goetzei, NOB—H. noblei, MAR—H. mariae, VIR—H. viridiflavus, GLA— H. glandicolor, MAG—H. marginatus, TUB—H. tuberculosa, BAN—H. bangwae, DIN—H. dintelmanni, MOR—H. marmoratus, NIT—H. nitidulus, SPA—H. spatzi, PAR—H. parallelus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="341" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1651,2037]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<bibRefCitation author="Poynton" box="[199,373,1723,1749]" firstAuthor="Poynton" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="37 - 41" refId="ref33660" refString="Poynton, J. C. (1977) A new Bufo and associated Amphibia from southern Tanzania. Annals of the Natal Museum, 23, 37 - 41." type="journal article" year="1977">Poynton (1977)</bibRefCitation>
recognised 
<taxonomicName box="[508,669,1723,1749]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[508,631,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from central 
<collectingCountry box="[818,919,1723,1749]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
with lateral black markings that show through the skin, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Schiotz" box="[329,494,1759,1785]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="269 - 276" refId="ref34209" refString="Schiotz, A. (1982) Two new Hyperolius (Anura) from Tanzania. Steenstrupia, 8, 269 - 276." type="journal article" year="1982">Schiøtz (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiotz" authorityYear="1982" box="[646,758,1759,1784]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="viridiflavus" variety="reesi">
<emphasis box="[646,758,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">H. v. reesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Poynton later (1991) recognised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiotz" authorityYear="1982" box="[1139,1323,1759,1785]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reesi">
<emphasis box="[1139,1323,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius reesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a good species. The dark lateral band is common in other species, as are yellow transverse stripes in some animals. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahl" box="[212,336,1831,1857]" firstAuthor="Ahl" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref28575" refString="Ahl, E. (1931) Zur Systematik der afrikanischen Arten der Baumfroschgattung Hyperolius (Amph. Anur.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1931">Ahl (1931)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[459,670,1831,1857]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetzei">
<emphasis box="[459,670,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius goetzei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[740,807,1831,1857]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Iringa</collectingRegion>
in central 
<collectingCountry box="[928,1032,1831,1857]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Schiotz" box="[1120,1287,1831,1857]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref34233" refString="Schiotz, A. (1999) Treefrogs of Africa. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 350 pp." type="book" year="1999">Schiøtz (1999)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated in colour from Dabaga near 
<collectingRegion box="[437,507,1867,1893]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Iringa</collectingRegion>
. The back is uniform with mottled sides. This species is known from central 
<collectingCountry name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schiotz" box="[200,353,1903,1929]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref34233" refString="Schiotz, A. (1999) Treefrogs of Africa. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 350 pp." type="book" year="1999">Schiøtz 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The localities of the 
<typeStatus box="[602,650,1903,1929]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">type</typeStatus>
and taxon regarded as a junior synonym are listed in 
<tableCitation box="[1249,1334,1903,1929]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="TABLE 3. Codes, localities and co-ordinates for the types and taxa now regarded as junior synonyms of the Hyperolius species, used in figs. 4–10." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF">Table 3</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1651,2037]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
The most common pattern elements in the descriptions of the 
<typeStatus box="[896,955,1939,1965]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">types</typeStatus>
included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[1096,1210,1939,1964]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetzei">
<emphasis box="[1096,1210,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">H. goetzei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are dorsal marbling (67%), followed by lateral marbling (33%), small dark spots (33%), or a dark lateral band (33%). The percentages are not additive, as the pattern elements may be shared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,151,214]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
The advertisement call (no voucher) is a series of frequency modulated whistles or clicks with a mean length of 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,218,187,213]" degrees="0.04" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" precision="555" value="-0.04">0.04 s</geoCoordinate>
and an emphasised frequency of 2239 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFF0270E659BFB74829F90FA:881B9983FFFF270E679CFF2983A990F9" box="[656,689,187,213]" country="Tanzania" latitude="-0.04" name="Hz" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" stateProvince="Iringa">Hz</location>
(
<collectingRegion box="[703,774,187,213]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Iringa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[785,891,187,214]" name="Tanzania" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
